## Day 22 — 08 Jun 2026 · Regression Testing the Week 3 UI Overhaul

### What I Did
Spent the day breaking things on purpose. Week 3 shipped a big desktop UI rebrand (sidebar, breadcrumb nav, role-based dashboards) — before building anything new on top of it, I went through every role (admin, teacher, student, parent) on tablet breakpoints specifically, since that's where flex/grid layouts tend to silently overflow first.

### What I Found & Fixed
- Sidebar overlapped the breadcrumb on `768px–820px` widths — a hardcoded `min-width` on the sidebar container instead of a `flex-shrink: 0`
- Two dashboards had table columns that didn't wrap, pushing the page into horizontal scroll

### Key Learnings
- Testing tablet widths specifically (not just "mobile" and "desktop") catches a category of bug that phone-sized testing misses entirely — the in-between widths are where rigid widths break first
- `flex-shrink: 0` vs `min-width` look similar in a flex container until the container itself gets squeezed — `min-width` wins and overflows, `flex-shrink: 0` just refuses to shrink below its content size

