## Day 27 — 13 Jun 2026 · QR Attendance — Testing Edge Cases

### What I Did
End-to-end tested the QR attendance flow with the kind of misuse a real classroom would produce: same student scanning twice, a QR code scanned after the teacher ended the session, and a stale QR code (from `Date.now() - ts` exceeding a max-age window).

### What I Found & Fixed
- Duplicate scans needed an explicit "already marked present" response instead of silently inserting a second attendance row
- An ended session needed to reject new scans with a clear message instead of marking attendance into a closed session

### Key Learnings
- "Happy path" testing (one student, one scan, works fine) tells you almost nothing about a feature like this — the real bugs only show up once you simulate the chaos of 30 phones hitting the same QR within a few seconds of each other
- A clear rejection message ("session has ended") is much better UX than a silent failure — the student needs to know to ask the teacher to mark them present manually

